          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The height and width of the underlying framebuffer object is calculated automatically by the view object based on its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiview/1622580-bounds"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiview/1622657-contentscalefactor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties and change whenever either of those properties change. Your application never directly adjusts the size of the framebuffer object. Instead, your application should read the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkview/1615559-drawableheight"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkview/1615591-drawablewidth"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties and use those to configure its OpenGL ES rendering code. For example, you might use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkview/1615559-drawableheight"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkview/1615591-drawablewidth"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties to set the OpenGL ES viewport, determining the size and complexity of the art assets to load, and so on."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
